# 1. Force consistent line endings (LF) for all text files
# This prevents issues if you're on Windows and a collaborator is on Linux/Mac
* text=auto eol=lf

# 2. Specifically mark code and web files
*.py text
*.html text
*.css text
*.md text
*.txt text

# 3. Handle binary files (images, icons)
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.ico binary

# 4. If you use Machine Learning models or Audio samples, 
# treat them as binary to prevent Git from trying to "fix" them
*.wav binary
*.mp3 binary
*.pth binary
*.pkl binary
*.h5 binary

# Language Statistics Overrides
# This tells GitHub to ignore these folders/files in the language bar
Static/* linguist-vendored
*.html linguist-vendored
*.css linguist-vendored

# You can also explicitly mark your app folder as the main focus
app/*.py linguist-detectable
